  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT214-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">tōḻi veṟiyāṭṭu eṭuttuk koṇṭaviṭattu aṟattoṭu niṉṟatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">The confidante standing firm in duty when the Veṟi dance
          was taken up. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT214">
        <lg type="edition">

          <l>maraṅkol kāṉavaṉ puṉantuḷarntu vittiya</l>
          <l>piṟaṅkukura liṟaṭi kākkum puṟantā</l>
          <l>ḻañci lōti yacaiyiyaṟ koṭicci</l>
          <l>tiruntiḻai yalkuṟkup peruntaḻai yutavic</l>
          <l>ceyalai muḻumuta loḻiya vayala</l>
          <l>taralai mālai cūṭṭi</l>
          <l>yēmuṟ ṟaṉṟiv vaḻuṅka lūrē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">


          <l>This noisy village has fallen into confusion,</l>
          <l rend="indent">adorning [itself] with chaplets of bowstring hemp</l>
          <l rend="indent2">from the neighbourhood, while the whole Aśoka stump stays behind</l>
          <l rend="indent3">which contributed [its] plentiful foliage for the hips,</l>
          <l rend="indent8">as a perfect decoration,</l>
          <l rend="indent">of the creeper woman with swinging gait [and] pretty, thin hair,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">hanging down [her] back, who guards the bright-eared millet,</l>
          <l rend="indent3">sown after the field was hoed by the tree-felling man</l>
          <l rend="indent10">from the wood.</l>

          <lg type="alternate" sameAs="6b" resp="#TVG">
            <l>[and] adorns [her] with chaplets of (red) Aralai flowers </l>
          </lg>

        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
